May we then argue that a little State will be
the better for being annexed by a large empire? Very
often it will. But the goodness of States does not
vary simply with their size: the little State may be
the better of the two. Justice also has to be 
considered, which does not permit us to do to our
neighbours, against their will, everything that we
take to be for their good.


